{"meta":{"updateDate":1755117017721,"pPcc":"SAT#P","questionId":"4b6f0a3f","skill_cd":"P.B.","score_band_range_cd":5,"skill_desc":"Nonlinear equations in one variable and systems of equations in two variables ","createDate":1755117017721,"program":"SAT","primary_class_cd_desc":"Advanced Math","ibn":"","external_id":"8c08419c-177e-4194-8d6c-68c4aa493232","primary_class_cd":"P","uId":"b34c61c1-ec70-4c8b-8f2c-f3801af973f3","difficulty":"M"},"source":"modern","detail":{"type":"spr","stem":"<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><math alttext=\"x squared minus 5 x minus 24 equals 0\"><mrow>\n\t<mrow>\n\t\t<msup>\n\t\t\t<mi>x</mi>\n\t\t\t<mn>2</mn>\n\t\t</msup>\n\t\t<mo>-</mo>\n\t\t<mrow>\n\t\t\t<mn>5</mn>\n\t\t\t<mi>x</mi>\n\t\t</mrow>\n\t\t<mo>-</mo>\n\t\t<mn>24</mn>\n\t</mrow>\n\t<mo>=</mo>\n\t<mn>0</mn>\n</mrow>\n</math></p>\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\">What is the sum of the solutions to the given equation?</p>","keys":["5"],"rationale":"<p>The correct answer is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"5\"><mn>5</mn></math>. The given quadratic equation can be rewritten in factored form as <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"left parenthesis x minus 8 right parenthesis left parenthesis x plus 3 right parenthesis equals 0\"><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>(</mo><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>)</mo><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>. Based on the zero product property, it follows that&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x minus 8 equals 0\"><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x plus 3 equals 0\"><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math>. Adding&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"8\"><mn>8</mn></math> to both sides of the equation&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x minus 8 equals 0\"><mi>x</mi><mo>-</mo><mn>8</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> yields&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x equals 8\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mn>8</mn></math>. Subtracting <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"3\"><mn>3</mn></math> from both sides of the equation&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x plus 3 equals 0\"><mi>x</mi><mo>+</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>=</mo><mn>0</mn></math> yields&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"x equals negative 3\"><mi>x</mi><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></math>. Therefore, the solutions to the given equation are <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"8\"><mn>8</mn></math> and <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"negative 3\"><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn></math>. It follows that the sum of the solutions to the given equation is <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"8 plus left parenthesis negative 3 right parenthesis\"><mn>8</mn><mo>+</mo><mo>(</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>3</mn><mo>)</mo></math>, or <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\" alttext=\"5\"><mn>5</mn></math>.</p>","externalid":"8c08419c-177e-4194-8d6c-68c4aa493232","correct_answer":["5"]}}